{"_id":"0ldRSChXaFIzXz14","name":"Heal","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph allows the user to heal [[/roll 1d6+3]] stamina either to themselves or to allies. The glyph may be activated in combat, but the user must be touching the target of the glyph for it to have effect.</p>","staminaCost":2,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"35UjD60NZLzfZB2Q","name":"Stupefy","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph makes a target being clumsy and disorientated. For [[/roll 1d6]] rounds it will be unable to pick up its weapon, make a coordinated attack or do anything else that requires physical coordination.</p>","staminaCost":5,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4CEu7lol3NIsjTNg","name":"Deafness","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph renders anyone nearby the user insidiously deaf. They don't notice the change, but may become aware of it depending on the circumstances. The glyph lasts [[/roll 1d6]] rounds, during which even the loudest noise cannot be heard by those so affected.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5ZukVV5vWs7QINgr","name":"Meld","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph can be used to meld two small items together, or to seal a door shut with a hand-span of fused material. The glyph makes a loud popping sound when manifesting.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"67uORmU5RvMKMgcg","name":"Inner Bond","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph allows the user to change the demeanour of one unfriendly target to one of friendship. It will not affect the target's allies, and the target will act as any other friendly being from that point on (i.e. if the target was attacked, it would become unfriendly once more).</p>","staminaCost":5,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"7SSle7Yqt4ILMO20","name":"Warp Strike","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This powerful offensive glyph sends an arcing lance of eldritch power toward the nearest target within nearby range. The attack automatically hits the nearest person, friend or foe, and inflicts [[/roll 1d6+2]] damage, [[/roll 1d6+4]] if the target is wearing appreciable amounts of metal. The bolt is bright blue and generates a crack, and is extremely obvious.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"7uQregXwFbCT8fug","name":"Esoteric Flame","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The user is able to manipulate warp resonance to set fire to something within nearby range that is flammable, as if a flaming torch had been held against it for several seconds. This can be used to set clothing alight. During activation, sparks are visible flying from the user's head toward the target.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"BvRyDEJkkWXG1XAa","name":"Stutter","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Stretching and kneading eldritch energies like glue, the user points at a target within nearby range who stutters out of reality and freezes in place for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds. The target cannot move from that place, although they can sway, move their arms etc. In combat the target can only attack those that come within range and all rolls suffer a penalty of -5 due to the hindering effect of the glyph.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DY83LxA9wH27y9EM","name":"Images","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>With this glyph the user is able to create an illusion that tricks the eyes of those that see it. The illusion has the maximum dimensions of a table and lasts [[/roll 1d6]] rounds. If the user stops doing anything else and concentrates solely on the manifestation, they may make the illusion move and produce sound.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"F9daBqvYSiHEXVks","name":"Dead Zone","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>When this glyph is activated, a zone of the blackest night expands around the user and all those in nearby range. The user and those creatures that can see in pitch black are unaffected. From the outside, the manifestation resembles a cloud of seething darkness.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"FzDOCSTnRO4RJeTt","name":"Doppelganger","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Once activated, this glyph creates an ethereal doppelganger of the user that will do their bidding. The creature is intelligent, silent, and deeply disturbing, but it is able to carry messages and items over vast distances (planetary range) for the user, travelling at warp speed, and may fetch small items that fit in the hand. The creature remains to haunt the user for [[/roll 1d6]] hours.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"GElBl5FUhbJkCaQN","name":"Burnout","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph will burnout any small, delicate electronic device, for example a computer, or the lock on an electronic door. The item will be destroyed by the warp energies, so it will be obvious that it has been tampered with.</p>","staminaCost":5,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"IA8YDNT7LnPbKOrA","name":"Glitch","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Flickering into the warp, a user who is falling from a height 'glitches' to the floor, escaping harm. A strong smell of ozone and crackling energy discharges remain.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Mc4hLXlgEtpHJYg3","name":"Scry","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>With this glyph, the user consults a crystal or other esoteric gewgaw and can see into the future. What they see is up to the games master, but it should be somewhat pertinent to the situation at hand.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Q851uDyjD5Bet76A","name":"Echoes","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Using ethereal energies, this glyph will create [[/roll 1d3]] copies of the user, which will mirror the actions of their parent. Enemies will not know which is the real user. The effect lasts [[/roll 1d6]] rounds.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"TAPUoVaQfKtmOTpH","name":"Ethereal Shield","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The user creates a suit of shimmering, ethereal amour about themselves. This counts as heavy armour, and lasts [[/roll 1d6]] rounds. It glows with enough light to act as a dim torch as well.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"TOXDsvAUtDPTCUsO","name":"Warp Path","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Using this glyph, the user is able to flit into the warp and re-appear within two metres of their original position. Great for moving through walls etc., but should the user rematerialize in a solid object, death is instantaneous.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"UhSwz6Nxm42Pl76s","name":"Hammer","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph gives the user enhanced strength, so that their melee attacks hit like hammer blows. In combat, if the user hits a target, roll the damage dice twice and take the better result. Lasts for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds of combat.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"VILA1tzgFFWAPPbG","name":"Warp Blast","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph generates a ball of negative warp energy that boils in the hand of the user, and may be flung at a single target within nearby range. It requires a successful ranged attack using the user's thrown skill against the target's dodge. On a successful hit, it inflicts [[/roll 2d6+2]] stamina damage and makes the target glow with discharging energy for [[/roll 1d3]] turns.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"VPaQsiEANvFf3XSa","name":"Deconstruct","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Using this glyph, the user is able to deconstruct the physical manifestation of a warp creature. Once activated, the user engages in a conflict of warp focus skill against any creatures that originated from the warp in nearby range. If successful, the beings are destroyed in a crackling discharge. If unsuccessful, the user suffers [[/roll 1d3]] stamina loss.</p>","staminaCost":5,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XInub4CnOZsbxh9Z","name":"Unquiet","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Swelling with ethereal might, the user projects a sense of fear that is palpable. All enemies in nearby range (i.e. not the user's allies) suffer a penalty of -3 to all tests due to fear for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds or until the user is next struck, whichever comes first.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XcPdAaVKTR6Ut4Bo","name":"Deny Gravity","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The user manipulates the warp to crack the laws of physics, and is able to rise ten meters into the air. The glyph lasts [[/roll 1d6]] rounds while the user concentrates, after which the user falls unless they are on stable ground. This glyph may not be used to arrest a fall.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XqgX4I6OeBpCl6OY","name":"Ether Scream","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Manifesting this glyph over an area nearby the user creates an ethereal alarm. Anyone entering who is not an ally of the user triggers the alarm, which is very loud. The alarm lasts one day, or until triggered.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"aKvCRFRm08XjQF5t","name":"Third Eye","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph allows the user to detect something within nearby range, so for example in the same room, that is hidden. The user can ask the games master to reveal a single thing hidden, which they must do. However that information is interpreted is up to the user.</p>","staminaCost":2,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"fO9eWVdYzNvDI8II","name":"Time Dilate","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>With a touch, the user slows time for the target, effectively doubling the speed of any one person, such that their movements appear as a blur. This has the specific effect in combat of allowing the target to take two actions in a round (so they can be selected to act twice), and giving them a bonus of +5 to attacks due to the whirling speed of their weapons. The glyph lasts [[/roll 1d6]] rounds, after which the target suffers loss of [[/roll 1d6]] stamina due to exhaustion.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"g02lYkjSXvX4jUrD","name":"Enhance","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Warp energies flow into any weapon, making it ethereal and thus able to damage beings normally only damaged by such things. The weapon will also inflict an additional [[/roll 1d6]] stamina damage in combat. The effect lasts for [[/roll 1d6]] turns, after which the device becomes burnt-out, brittle and breaks. Can be used with guns which are destroyed after the manifestation ends.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hXccjg8FFCE1JIZM","name":"Scour","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Using insidious warp energies, the user can read the surface thoughts of a being within nearby range. Only general impressions can be gained (for example, hostile intent but not exactly what action this will produce). To outside observers except the target this manifestation appears as crackling line of energy connecting user and target for a few moments.</p>","staminaCost":5,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hfnrywYsoWMJlSIN","name":"Crack","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The user creates a crack in reality that acts like a wall between themselves and a target. The crack is two metres high and wide, and may be used to block an entranceway. The wall lasts [[/roll 1d6]] minutes, and cannot be penetrated by physical items or beings. It may by penetrated by warp energy.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jG3K1IimHDaPM8N0","name":"Miasma","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>When activated this glyph creates a cloud of warp energies that destructively interacts with living matter. Any being, friend or foe, within nearby range loses [[/roll 1d6]] stamina. Only the user is blissfully resistant to the hideous energies.</p>","staminaCost":5,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jSosxES12itgeFiy","name":"Master","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph allows the user to take over the minds of unintelligent creatures. If successfully activated, the user has complete control of the creatures mind and may direct it to act as they will, except when this would be obviously damaging to the creature. The glyph lasts [[/roll 1d6]] rounds, which the games master rolls in secret.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"lT2F5LKxODpV4e0v","name":"Trance","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This glyph renders a target into a trance-like sleep for [[/roll 1d6]] minutes. The user must touch the target, which in combat requires a successful brawling attack. When the target awakes it will have no idea what happened.</p>","staminaCost":5,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"p5tFHnDGku3Vh5vM","name":"Poison","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>A target touched by the user suddenly becomes convinced they are poisoned. They fall prone, wretching for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds before the suggestion subsides.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ps0nRi4BuP61XdZn","name":"Speak","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The user can use this glyph to speak to an intelligent creature as if he knew their language. The user will understand what they say, and his words will be automatically translated. Lasts for [[/roll 1d6]] minutes.</p>","staminaCost":3,"test":{"value":"Opposed","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"u3C25Un2FPpDMN5r","name":"Negative Warp","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>After manifesting this glyph, the user is surrounded by a golden hued glow. For the next [[/roll 1d6]] rounds, the user may make a standard warp focus test to dispel any glyph manifestations that occurs nearby, even those that don't target them. If they are successful, the manifestation is dissipated, if not its effects occur as normal.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"y62jO1Zq1UpZfFqa","name":"Vermin","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Using an eldritch calling, the user summons an infestation of warp vermin. These chitinous creatures fill a space nearby the user, and remain a seething, tumultuous mass for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds, before they dissipate.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zq5XCC1RXQqUtBWt","name":"Unseen","type":"Glyph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/items/spells/wind-hole.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Bending the warp like a lense, this glyph renders the user invisible to any enemies in nearby range at the time of manifesting, although they still make sounds. The user's allies can still see them, as can other enemies who appear later. The glyph lasts [[/roll 1d6]] minutes, which the games master rolls in secret. There is no obvious sign that the user is no longer invisible. While invisible, enemies attacking the user suffer a penalty of -5 to attack rolls.</p>","staminaCost":4,"test":{"value":"Basic","choices":{"Basic":"Basic","Opposed":"Opposed"}}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZtfDqSvKTGtngaYG":3},"flags":{}}
